08/10/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Milka Planinc, who was prime minister of the former Yugoslavia during the 1980s, has died at the age of 86, news agencies reported, quoting family sources. According to the reports, Planinc died in a Zagreb hospital Thursday (October 7th) after a long illness. A close associate of long-time President Josip Broz Tito, she was the first female prime minister from the ranks of a communist party, serving from 1982 to 1986. (HINA, AP - 07/10/10)
